article.headline: Brown 62, Maine 54
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Peter Sullivan scored eight of his 21 points in the final 2:18 as Brown defeated Maine 62-54 on Saturday. Sullivan's layup with 1:02 remaining broke the game's sixth tie and put the Bears (4-3) ahead to stay, 56-54. The senior forward was 4 for 4 from the free-throw line over the final 14 seconds and was 13 for 13 from the line in the game. Brown led 25-19 with 3:35 left in the first half, but Maine (2-4) pulled ahead 34-27 with a 15-2 run that spanned halftime. A 3-pointer by Adrian Williams gave Brown its first lead of the second half, 41-40 at the 12:18 mark. Murphy Burnatowski led Maine with 15 points, 12 in the first half. Raheem Singleton added 11, with nine in the second half. Tucker Halpern scored 12 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for Brown.
